  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Even the suffering is forgotten.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so it is understandable that a culture in, in Hungary was so dominantly [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] created, maintained, and managed by Jews.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] To return to the-- to the educational system in Kisvarda, then they were, beyond the Talmud Torah, an-- another grade, so to say, which was considered the Yeshiva K'Tana or the junior high, or, perhaps, junior college.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] These were, again, privately run [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] institutions, if you can call them that, because usually what they were-- as were the kindergarten levels also-- they would have room in the home of a particular teacher, who, as I say, derived his living from the teaching and from the fees that his students paid him.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then beyond that, in, in Kisvarda, unlike in some other places where famous rabbis maintain what-- permanently what were known as yeshiva, which you might call graduate schools, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] we had a-- only occasionally, when our local chief rabbi, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I think, was ill, sort of the yeshiva petered out.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But the, the interesting thing about this system is-- as well as the life of the community and its organization and structure-- is that it was all contiguous.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was all one.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "All of the stores on Main Street, with rarest exception, were Jewishly owned.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Then, if you turn to the right on Start Street, it was for at least, I would say, a mile, all Jewish residences and institutions.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You could go on one side of Start Street and literally go in the backyard of these institutions through that mile or a mile and a half and feel nothing but Jewish institutions and Jewish homes.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
